{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape3D\/points"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape3D\/godotClassName"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ConvexPolygonShape3D","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A 3D convex polyhedron shape, intended for use in physics. Usually used to provide a shape for a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CollisionShape3D"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape3D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"solid","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", which means it detects collisions from objects that are fully inside it, unlike "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConcavePolygonShape3D","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" which is hollow. This makes it more suitable for both detection and physics."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Convex decomposition:"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" A concave polyhedron can be split up into several convex polyhedra. This allows dynamic physics bodies to have complex concave collisions (at a performance cost) and can be achieved by using several ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape3D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" nodes. To generate a convex decomposition from a mesh, select the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/MeshInstance3D","type":"reference"},{"text":" node, go to the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mesh"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" menu that appears above the viewport, and choose ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create Multiple Convex Collision Siblings"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":". Alternatively, ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/MeshInstance3D\/createMultipleConvexCollisions(settings:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be called in a script to perform this decomposition at run-time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Performance:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConvexPolygonShape3D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is faster to check collisions against compared to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConcavePolygonShape3D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", but it is slower than primitive collision shapes such as "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SphereShape3D","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BoxShape3D"},{"type":"text","text":". Its use should generally be limited to medium-sized objects that cannot have their collision accurately represented by primitive shapes."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot20ConvexPolygonShape3DC","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"ConvexPolygonShape3D","symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"ide